The paper discusses the use of SAT solvers in AI planning, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also delves into the structure and hardness of planning problems, which could be categorized under Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) and Programming Languages (cs.PL). The use of DPLL-based procedures is a key aspect of the paper, which could be classified under Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Computational Complexity (cs.CC).
